radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: Computed Tomography (CT) scan of the brain
radiographic_examinations.findings: Acute left subdural hematoma in patient 1; simple parietal skull fracture and small, underlying acute subdural hemorrhage in patient 2; small, acute subdural hematoma over the convexities and falx in patient 3.

Abnormalities consistent with Osteogenesis Imperfecta and a healing, nondisplaced oblique fracture of the distal left tibia and each ulna in patient 1; generalized osteopenia and a healing left posterior rib and femur fractures in patient 2; normal in patient 3.
